"'''Laughter After Dark'''" is a short story written by [[Patricia A. Jackson]] that was originally published in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 15|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 15]] by [[West End Games]] in [[November]] [[1997]].

==Plot summary==
On the seventh [[Standard year/Legends|anniversary]] of [[Death/Legends|death]] of his beloved [[Saahir Ru'luv]], [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] [[Thaddeus Ross]] visits [[Reuther's Wetdock]] [[Cantina/Legends|tavern]] and has a lonely sad [[Alcohol/Legends|drink]]. Ross remembers an unpleasant event when Saahir seduced him into [[Transport/Legends|transporting]] [[Weapon/Legends|weaponry]] for the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]], a mission he wanted no part of. The mission turned sour when he discovered that Saahir was engaged to a Rebel [[Commander/Legends|commander]]. Though he was heartbroken and angry, his partner, [[Trep Winterrs|Trep]], convinced him to continue the mission for the [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]]. Tragedy followed when the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]] attacked the Rebel outpost just as they completed delivery of the cargo to Saahir and her fiancé. Saahir suffered mortal wounds and, with her dying breath, and in his arms, admitted she loved Ross all along and asked him to find the strength one day to forgive her. Seven years later, Ross finally does, mourning her loss.

